==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pledget
<hw>Pledg"et</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prov. E., a small
plug.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small plug.</def> <mark>[Prov.
End.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A string of oakum used in
calking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A compress, or small flat tent of
lint, laid over a wound, ulcer, or the like, to exclude air, retain
dressings, or absorb the matter discharged.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plegepoda</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
